definition:
Let $(A,d)$ and $(A^{'},d^{'})$ be chain complexes. A *chain map*
$f:A \to A^{'}$ is a sequence of homomorphisms $\{f_n\}$ such that
$d_{n}^{'} \circ f_{n} =  f_{n-1} \circ d_{n}$ for each $n$.
Diagramatically, this says that the following diagram commutes:
$$\xymatrix{
& A_{n} \ar[d]^{f_n} \ar[r]^{d_{n}} & A_{n-1} \ar[d]^{f_{n-1}} \\
& A_{n}^{'} \ar[r]^{d_{n}^{'}} & A_{n-1}^{'}
}$$
